I didn't quite understand the problem you described in #861.

My understanding is that if the user submits either a Runnable or Callable via `ThreadPoolExecutor.submit`, then `UncaughtExceptionHandler` is irrelevant and won't be invoked. Any `Throwable` thrown by the Runnable/Callable will be wrapped into `ExecutionException` in the `Future` returned by `submit`.

If the user submits a Runnable via `ThreadPoolExecutor.execute`, then any `Throwable` thrown by the Runnable can be retrieved in `afterExecute`. 

So I'm not sure why `ErrorHandlingThreadFactory` is needed. In fact if I understand correctly, `UncaughtExceptionHandler` is only useful if you run a thread manually (not via `ExecutorService` so I'm not even sure whether we need `UncaughtExceptionHandler` in the first place).
